Your hands give clues to ‘brain sex’ — the way your brain reflects your gender . 
  According to popular mythology men tend to be more obsessed by cars and obscure facts . 
  Women are said to be better at empathy and understanding what another person is feeling . 
  In the SBS One series Horizon Professor Alice Roberts and Dr Michael Mosley examine the links between gender and the brain . 
  Some skills and interests are considered more typically male . 
  Others are described as more typically female and occur more commonly in women . 
  Empathisers are more typically ‘female’ brained as they are typically women . 
 